---
import GitHubIcon from "../components/GitHubIcon.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const demoUrl = "https://demo.aictx.dev/?token=demo";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main id="top">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-panel">
        <a class="eyebrow-link" href="https://github.com/MicrexIT/aictx" rel="noreferrer">
          <GitHubIcon />
          Local-first and open source
        </a>
        <h1 class="hero-title">
          <span class="hero-title-desktop">Stop re&#8209;explaining your</span>
          <span class="hero-title-desktop">repo to AI agents.</span>
          <span class="hero-title-mobile">Stop re&#8209;explaining</span>
          <span class="hero-title-mobile">your repo to AI agents.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-copy">
          <span>Set it up once. Your repo keeps the reminders.</span>
          <span>Agents load the right context before work.</span>
        </p>

        <div class="hero-install" aria-label="Install Aictx">
          <div class="hero-command" aria-label="Quick start command">
            <code>npm install -g @aictx/memory</code>
          </div>

          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/MicrexIT/aictx" rel="noreferrer">Install Aictx</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="split-section" id="context" aria-labelledby="context-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="context-title">Durable memory beats bigger prompts.</h2>
        <p>
          AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md files can help, but they should stay small.
          Aictx adds the durable memory behind them: set up the repo once, let agents
          load only the relevant reminders, and save new decisions when they should last.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="comparison">
        <div>
          <strong>Set up once</strong>
          <p>Write conservative starter memory and repo guidance in one first-run workflow.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Quiet reminders</strong>
          <p>Agents pull product intent, conventions, workflows, and gotchas when the task needs them.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Reviewable memory</strong>
          <p>Store memory as local files that fit normal Git review and rollback.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="impact-section" id="before-after" aria-labelledby="before-after-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="before-after-title">Project memory for Codex.</h2>
        <p>
          Load context before work. Inspect memory. Review changes like code.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="impact-module impact-module-single" style="--reveal: 48%">
        <div class="impact-visual">
          <div class="impact-visual-panel is-active" id="impact-context" data-impact-panel="impact-context">
            <div class="comparison-labels" aria-hidden="true">
              <span>Before</span>
              <span>After</span>
            </div>
            <div class="comparison-state" aria-hidden="true">Compare</div>
            <div class="scene-layer before">
              <div class="codex-chat codex-chat-before" aria-label="Codex chat without Aictx">
                <div class="codex-chat-topbar">
                  <span>Update viewer search behavior</span>
                  <strong>•••</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-user-bubble">
                  <p>Can you polish viewer search?</p>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-work-pill">Worked for 7m 18s⌄</div>
                <div class="codex-divider"></div>
                <div class="codex-response">
                  <p>I need to inspect the docs and viewer code to recover the product direction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-command-row">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
                  Ran <code>rg "viewer|search|schema|facets"</code>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-command-row">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
                  Read <code>docs/viewer.md</code>, <code>viewer/src/App.svelte</code>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-command-row muted-row">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
                  Explored 11 files, 4 searches
                </div>
                <div class="codex-response warning-message">
                  <p>Remind me: are we still avoiding dashboard-style UI here?</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="scene-layer after">
              <div class="codex-chat codex-chat-after" aria-label="Codex chat with Aictx">
                <div class="codex-chat-topbar">
                  <span>Update viewer search behavior</span>
                  <strong>•••</strong>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-user-bubble">
                  <p>Can you polish viewer search?</p>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-command-row aictx-command-row">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
                  Ran <code>aictx load "improve viewer search UI"</code>
                </div>
                <div class="aictx-context-pack">
                  <span>AI Context Pack</span>
                  <strong>Viewer memory page shows canonical types, facets, scopes, and relations first.</strong>
                  <p>Keep guided lenses secondary. Verify schema filters and relation boundaries.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="codex-command-row muted-row">
                  <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
                  Loaded 6 relevant memories before editing
                </div>
                <div class="codex-response ready-message">
                  <p>I have the UI constraint and verification path. I’ll update search without reopening old decisions.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="reveal-divider" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <input
              class="reveal-scrubber"
              type="range"
              min="0"
              max="100"
              value="48"
              aria-label="Slide between before and after for context loading"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="workflow" id="workflow" aria-labelledby="workflow-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="workflow-title">How it works</h2>
        <p>
          Aictx keeps the everyday loop small after the first setup: agents load
          relevant reminders, do the work, then save durable knowledge for later review.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="workflow-loop" aria-label="Aictx everyday loop">
        <span>set up once</span>
        <span>load relevant reminders</span>
        <span>do the work</span>
      </div>

      <div class="steps">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <p class="step-label">Once per repo</p>
          <h3>Create the memory layer.</h3>
          <p>Aictx writes starter memory and short agent guidance so the repo can remind future sessions what matters.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <p class="step-label">Before work</p>
          <h3>Load the right reminders.</h3>
          <p>The model starts with product intent, repo conventions, known traps, and the verification path already in view.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <p class="step-label">After work</p>
          <h3>Save what future sessions should remember.</h3>
          <p>Useful decisions and gotchas become local memory files that humans can inspect, diff, commit, or roll back.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="demo-section" id="demo" aria-labelledby="demo-title">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2 id="demo-title">Inspect real Todo App memory bodies.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-art">
        <a class="viewer-frame" href={demoUrl} rel="noreferrer">
          <span class="browser-bar">
            <i></i>
            <i></i>
            <i></i>
            <code>demo.aictx.dev</code>
          </span>
          <img
            src="/assets/viewer-demo.png"
            alt="Aictx viewer showing a selected Todo App memory object with properties and Markdown body content open."
          />
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-footer">
        <p>Browse a generic Todo App project with canonical object types, facet categories, inline Markdown bodies, relations, and provenance links.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href={demoUrl} rel="noreferrer">
          Open live demo
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <script>
    const revealControls = document.querySelectorAll(".reveal-scrubber");

    for (const control of revealControls) {
      const module = control.closest(".impact-module");
      const setReveal = () => {
        module?.style.setProperty("--reveal", `${control.value}%`);
        module?.style.setProperty("--handle", `clamp(28px, ${control.value}%, calc(100% - 28px))`);
        const state = control.closest("[data-impact-panel]")?.querySelector(".comparison-state");
        if (state) {
          state.textContent =
            control.value === "0" ? "Showing after" : control.value === "100" ? "Showing before" : "Compare";
        }
      };

      control.addEventListener("input", setReveal);
      if (control.closest("[data-impact-panel]")?.classList.contains("is-active")) {
        setReveal();
      }
    }
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
